          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"kubernetes/kubernetes\", \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/preflight/checks.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"kubernetes/kubernetes\", \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/factory/etcd3.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/config.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/client.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/doc.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/lease.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/maintenance.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/config/config.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdmain/config.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdmain/grpc_proxy.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdmain/etcd.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/server.go\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/config.go\", \"symbol\": \"Config.DialTimeout\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/config/config.go\", \"symbol\": \"ServerConfig.PeerDialTimeout\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdmain/config.go\", \"symbol\": \"configProxy.ProxyDialTimeoutMs\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go\", \"symbol\": \"Transport.DialTimeout\"}\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"kubernetes/kubernetes\", \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/factory/etcd3.go\", \"symbol\": \"create\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/config.go\", \"symbol\": \"Config\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"client/v3/client.go\", \"symbol\": \"dialWithBalancer\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/config/config.go\", \"symbol\": \"PeerDialTimeout\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\", \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go\", \"symbol\": \"NewRoundTripper\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"DialTimeout configuration is used across the Kubernetes and etcd ecosystems to control connection establishment timeouts. In the Kubernetes apiserver, two files reference DialTimeout: checks.go in the preflight checks uses net.DialTimeout for connection validation, and etcd3.go in the storage backend factory configures the etcd client with appropriate DialTimeout values from the Config struct. In etcd client/v3, the Config struct defines DialTimeout as a time.Duration field that controls the maximum duration for failing to establish a connection. This timeout is used throughout the client package: in client.go it's used to set context deadlines during dial operations (lines 312-314, 447-448, 492-495), in lease.go it's used to calculate keepAliveTimeout for lease operations (line 192), and in maintenance.go it's used similarly for token acquisition (lines 89-90). The documentation in doc.go includes example usage showing DialTimeout set to 5 seconds. On the server side, the configuration is split: server/config/config.go defines the PeerDialTimeout() method on ServerConfig that calculates peer connection timeout based on election ticks (lines 321-323), while server/etcdmain/config.go defines ProxyDialTimeoutMs as a uint millisecond configuration (line 70 and default 1000ms on line 105). The proxy dial timeout is used in grpc_proxy.go and etcd.go to configure HTTP timeout transports. The rafthttp transport layer in server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go defines a DialTimeout field on the Transport struct (line 100) that specifies the maximum duration for dial operations, which is passed to NewRoundTripper and newStreamRoundTripper functions (lines 135-139). Finally, in server/etcdserver/server.go, the PeerDialTimeout() method is used to configure both rafthttp RoundTripper initialization and the Transport struct's DialTimeout field (lines 401, 689).\"\n}\n",
